      • equals

        public boolean equals​(Player otherPlayer)
        Player equality is defined by UUIDs. Player objects are considered equal if they share a UUID. This does not guarantee that the rest of their fields are the same. Two instances of the same player might have discrepencies due to dirty reads or concurrency issues, but nonetheless be 'equal'.
        Parameters:
        otherPlayer - The player to compare equality to.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the two objects represent the same player (i.e. share a UUID), returns false otherwise.
